{
  "texts": [
    "Before the transformer, human parity was far beyond reach.",
    "For details, see (Bottou, 2012).",
    "AsGubelmann (2023, p. 492) summarizes it, \"Briefly, the method computes the gradient of the loss function with respect to the model's parameters and then optimizes the parameters by \"moving\" them in the appropriate direction of the gradient (that is, \"downwards\", to minimize the loss).",
    "As a computation of the full loss function would be computationally too expensive, the method only computes the loss for a sample set of data points and extrapolates from there (true to its name: \"stochastic\").\"",
    "For an informal, practice-oriented introduction to the model, see Khalid (2019).123"
  ]
}